node.title: ‘Succession’ Recap, Season 3, Episode 6: Pretenders to the Throne
node.description: Kendall had hoped to be the kingmaker, but we all know whom that role belongs to.

node.title: 'We miss you Mommy': What is happening with Monaco's Princess Charlene?
node.description: Princess Charlene's long-awaited return to Monaco is cut short ahead of major celebrations in the wealthy nation. Here's what we know about it.

node.title: Sudan's military reinstates ousted civilian PM
node.description: Sudan's civilan Prime Minister has appeared on TV to sign a new power-sharing agreement with coup leader General Abdel Fattah al-Burhan.

node.title: Justin Bieber urged to cancel concert in Saudi Arabia in protest over human rights record
node.description: Pop star Justin Bieber faces growing calls to cancel a concert in Saudi Arabia over the Kingdom's human rights record. The fiancee of slain Saudi critic Jamal Khashoggi joins a chorus of voices urging him not to perform.

node.title: Schoolies 'aren't as drunk as they used to be', authorities say
node.description: Police say this year's crop of school leavers are "actually the best", with bad behaviour of all kinds down on previous years and "toolies" making up the majority of the weekend's arrests.

node.title: FedEx workers locked out as industrial dispute intensifies ahead of Christmas delivery rush
node.description: FedEx locks workers out as an ongoing industrial dispute threatens parcel deliveries in the run-up to Black Friday sales and Christmas.

node.title: First-term MP to replace Vickie Chapman as Attorney-General in SA Government
node.description: Adelaide Hills backbencher MP Josh Teague will be sworn in as South Australia's Attorney-General tomorrow, replacing Vickie Chapman.

node.title: Katherine lockdown extended as NT records two new local COVID cases
node.description: The Northern Territory has recorded two new local cases of COVID-19 overnight, Chief Minister Michael Gunner says.

node.title: Police reduce capabilitiy to investigate work-related fatal road crashes
node.description: Documents reveal police have reduced their capability to investigate fatal road crashes for work-related health and safety breaches.

node.title: Protesters at Shelly Bay in Wellington say they will remain at site
node.description: The group occupying Shelly Bay in Wellington say they will remain at the site following last week's police presence.

node.title: Police do not suspect foul play in disappearance of Cindy Li
node.description: Police in Auckland say they do not believe there was any foul play in relation to the disappearance of Sandringham woman Cindy Li who was missing for 12 days before being located near her home.

node.title: Kyle Rittenhouse Tells Tucker Carlson He Backs BLM, Shooting Had 'Nothing To Do With Race'
node.description: "I'm not a racist person. I support the BLM movement. I support peacefully demonstrating," Rittenhouse said during his first TV appearance since his acquittal.

node.title: Paine back on the field, and appealing for Test selection as sexting scandal rolls on
node.description: Former Australian Test captain Tim Paine is back behind the stumps in his first game in months, as the sexting scandal which cost him the role continues to play out.

node.title: Gold Coast infectious diseases expert revealed as Queensland's new chief health officer
node.description: Gold Coast infectious diseases expert John Gerrard is named as Queensland's next chief health officer, becoming the permanent replacement for Jeannette Young.

node.title: El Salvador's President reveals plan for volcano-powered 'Bitcoin City'
node.description: In a rock concert-like atmosphere, Nayib Bukele uses a gathering of bitcoin enthusiasts to launch his latest idea: a seaside "Bitcoin City" at the base of a volcano.

node.title: 'That's a loophole': Queensland health authorities to examine gap in testing rules for interstate hotspot visits
node.description: Acting Chief Health Officer Peter Aitken says there is a "loophole" in the state's roadmap that would allow Queenslanders to visit hotspot locations interstate and return without being tested for COVID while they are there.

node.title: Police respond to serious incident in Hawke's Bay
node.description: Police are responding to a serious incident which has forced two schools in Hastings into lockdown.

node.title: Confusion from government over taking the pulse for Covid-19
node.description: Health officials and government ministers are at odds over whether every household isolating with a positive Covid-19 case should get a critical device which measures their oxygen levels.

node.title: Multiple people injured after SUV plows through Wisconsin holiday parade
node.description: The chief of police said more than 20 people were injured and that the SUV has been located.

node.title: Fauci Says Families With Fully Vaccinated Kids Won't Need to Wear Masks on Christmas
node.description: "Get vaccinated and you can enjoy the holidays very easily. And if you're not, please be careful," said. Dr. Anthony Fauci, as COVID-19 climbed nationally after months of decline.

node.title: Multiple people injured as SUV ploughs through Christmas parade in Wisconsin
node.description: More than 20 people have been injured after an SUV sped through a Christmas parade in Waukesha, Wisconsin.

node.title: Police investigating 'specific threats' against politicians, AFP commissioner says
node.description: Australia's top cop reveals his officers spent the weekend investigating threats made against politicians, as concerns about violence directed towards parliamentarians intensify.

node.title: NZ and Moana Super Rugby squads confirmed for 2022
node.description: The five New Zealand Super Rugby sides along with Moana Pasifika have finalised their squads for the 2022 Super Rugby Pacific competition.

node.title: Gunman kills one in Jerusalem's Old City
node.description: A gunman killed one person and wounded three others in Jerusalem's Old City on Sunday before being shot dead by Israeli police, a police spokesperson said, describing it as a terrorist attack.

node.title: Five injured as bus crashes into fence in Lower Hutt
node.description: Five passengers received minor injuries when a bus crashed into a fence in Lower Hutt.

node.title: Searching for the truth in Emperor Caligula's gardens in Rome
node.description: When workers began excavating a new parking garage in Rome, they discovered what archeologists say was once Emperor Caligula's pleasure gardens. Anderson Cooper reports on the find and the scholarly re-examination of Caligula's legacy.

node.title: The race to put supersonic flights back in the sky
node.description: Nearly 20 years after the Concorde made its final commercial flight, new efforts are underway to make supersonic passenger travel viable again.

node.title: Reimagining police departments with safety and justice in mind
node.description: Scott Pelley reports on the ways American cities are reimagining their police departments, with Austin, Texas, leading the way.

node.title: Driver Plows S.U.V. Into Holiday Parade in Wisconsin
node.description: A witness said the vehicle sped down the street as the parade, in Waukesha, Wis., near Milwaukee, was going on. It was not clear how many people were injured.

node.title: Man Dies in Freak Accident as Four Jet Skis Collide in California: Police
node.description: Emergency responders attempted to perform CPR at the scene, but the man was pronounced dead shortly after.
